[A] China: National Health Commission, 83 611 total cases, 4634 deaths
Date: Tue 14 Jul 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in Chinese, machine trans., abridged, edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqtb/202007/05c60da379bf43cd9162d90bc01c50dc.shtml


On 14 Jul 2020 (as of midnight 15 Jul 2020):
- 6 new cases of confirmed infections (all were imported cases: Shanghai municipality (3), Shanxi province (1), Chongqing province (1), and Yunnan province (1)), no new cases of suspected infections, and no deaths.
- A total of 1988 imported cases have been reported.
- 83 611 confirmed cases and 4634 deaths; 78 693 recovered and discharged from hospital; 767 432 close contacts with infected patients; and 3577 are under medical observation.
- 4 new asymptomatic cases (all imported); no asymptomatic cases confirmed as symptomatic; 110 asymptomatic cases under medical observation (including 87 imported cases).
- 1569 cases in Hong Kong [an increase of 100 cases since 13 Jul 2020], 46 in Macau.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
and
ProMED-mail rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[The 6 new confirmed cases in the past 24 hours were all imported, and no new cases have been reported from Beijing for 9 days.

There were 4 newly confirmed infections in asymptomatic individuals (all imported) and no new conversions from asymptomatic to symptomatic in the past 24 hours. Since 18 May 2020, China has reported 37 cases of conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic infection.

Hong Kong reported 100 new cases. As of 4 PM on 14 Jul 2020 (local time), there was information on 48 newly confirmed cases. Of those, there were 27 males and 21 females aged between 6 and 90 years and 8 had a travel history during the incubation period. (https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/202007/14/P2020071400955.htm). In addition, there is a report of a nosocomial cluster of 3 confirmed cases and potentially 44 ontacts of other patients and 27 healthcare worker contacts. (https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/202007/14/P2020071400906.htm).

Takeaway message: China continues to have importations of infected individuals with SARS-CoV-2. Hong Kong is dealing with increased local transmission associated with the lifting of restrictions -- new severe restrictions announced.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://sacu.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/provmap.png and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7576001,155. - Mod.MPP]

