[In the past 24 hours, according to the report at the source URL, the tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Korea has increased by 39 cases with no new deaths, compared with 33 cases and no deaths in the previous day (13 Jul 2020). The daily newly confirmed case count has been at or below 100 for 92 consecutive days. There were 11 locally transmitted cases: Seoul (6), Gyeonggi (3), Gwangju (1), and Daejeon (1); and 28 imported cases: airport quarantine (23), Gyeonggi (2), Daejeon (2) and Incheon (1). There were 12 provinces reporting no newly confirmed cases (compared with 11 provinces yesterday, 11 Jul 2020).

The overall impression hasn't changed. Lifting of measures has been accompanied by increases in locally acquired infections through increasing clusters related to gatherings of people at employment (bringing it outside employment to contacts) and in places of worship, and bars and clubs. However, that being said, importations are also playing a major role in the country as well. New clusters seem to be controlled fairly quickly due to excellent contact tracing activities, a key to maintaining control.

A map of South Korea showing provinces can be seen at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/korea-south-administrative-map.htm and a HealthMap/ProMED map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7576001,195.- Mod.MPP]

