[The tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Italy is up by +114 cases and +17 deaths in the past 24 hours. The previous day's (13 Jul 2020) 24-hour change was +169 cases and +13 deaths. The numbers of hospitalized cases and cases in intensive care units are still in a slow decline.

Cases still continue to be concentrated in Lombardy, the original epicenter of the outbreak (see tables at the link on the source URL to "download the latest data"). Lombardy again reported the largest number of newly confirmed cases in the 24-hour period (30) -- the lowest reported by Lombardy in months; Veneto (19), Lazio (18), Sicily (15), and Emilia-Romagna (13), are the other provinces reporting 10 or more cases A total of 16 provinces reported fewer than 10 newly confirmed cases (9 provinces reported no new cases). Italy is now 69 days post phase 2 initial opening up and 53 days post 2nd stage of phase 2 opening up. For more detailed information on the outbreak, I suggest going to the source URL above.

