[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 215.

In the 24 hours since the last WHO update:

- The Americas region reported 56.2% of the global newly reported cases and 51.0% of newly reported deaths for this 24-hour period, maintaining its dominance as the most severely affected region, although a drop in proportional representation from prior days. The USA reported 54.4% (60 113) of the newly confirmed cases in the region, and Brazil reported 22.5% (24 831), Colombia 4.6% (5083), Mexico 4.1% (4482), Peru 3.3% (3616), Argentina 2.4% (2657), and Chile 2.4% (2616).

- The European region reported 10.5% of the global newly reported cases and 10.3% of the newly confirmed deaths globally. Russia reported 30.2% (6248) of the regional newly confirmed cases, followed by Spain 9.9% (2045), Kazakhstan 9.0% (1856), Israel 6.2% (1279), France 5.4% (1115), Turkey 4.9% (1008), Sweden 4.5% (9.8), Uzbekistan 3.3% (679), Ukraine 3.1% (638), the UK 2.6% (530), Azerbaijan 2.6% (529), Kyrgyzstan 2.0% (421), and Romania 2.0% (413).

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 8.0% of the global newly reported cases and 14.4% of global newly reported fatalities. Saudi Arabia reported 18.2% (2852) of the regional newly reported cases, followed by Iran 15.0% (2349), Iraq 14.2% (2229), Oman 13.8% (2164), Pakistan 12.6% (1979), Egypt 6.0% (931), Kuwait 3.9% (614), Bahrain 3.4% (535), and Qatar 2.7% (418).

- The African region reported 7.7% of the global newly reported cases and 4.9% of newly reported fatalities. South Africa reported 76.6% (11 554) of the newly reported cases in the region in the past 24 hours, followed by Nigeria 3.9% (595), Algeria 3.3% (494), Ghana 3.1% (470), and Zambia 2.6% (388).

- The Western Pacific region reported 0.87% of the global newly reported cases and 1.8% of global deaths. The Philippines reported 43.7% (747) of the newly reported cases in the region (a significant drop), followed by Japan 20.6% (352), Singapore 18.8% (322), Australia 10.7% (183), China 3.2% (55), and South Korea 1.9% (33).

- The South East Asia region reported 16.8% of the global newly reported cases and 17.7% of global deaths. India reported 86.1% (28 498) of newly reported cases in the region, followed by Bangladesh 9.4% (3099), Indonesia 3.9% (1282), and Nepal 0.44% (144).

Impression: Caution in interpretation of individual country standings as data reflect reporting on Mon 13 Jul 2020 and most likely have weekend artifact. That being said, the overall picture is basically the same. The ordering of the regions has the Americas having the highest disease load and newly confirmed cases on a daily basis, followed by the South East Asia region, then Europe followed by the Eastern Mediterranean, followed by the Africa region and the Western Pacific representing the lowest daily caseload of all of the regions.

Figure 2. Epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases, by date of report and WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 14 Jul 2020, at the source URL above, is an excellent visual representation of the epidemic as described in the above text. - Mod.MPP]

